comments: Portis (MIL) is moving alongside Thomas' (BKN) path and legally contests his driving shot attempt.
Simmons (BKN) is moving alongside Middleton's (MIL) path as he defends the drive to the basket.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) legally contests Bridges' (BKN) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) is already in Finney-Smith's (BKN) path and is firming up over his left leg when marginal contact occurs.
Thomas (BKN) brings his forearm towards Antetokounmpo's (MIL) front, and the contact during his shot near the rim is marginal.
Crowder (MIL) legally contests Thomas' (BKN) jump shot attempt.
Simmons (BKN) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to the Bucks.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) and Simmons (BKN) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) and Finney-Smith (BKN) come together at the same spot in transition, and marginal lower body contact occurs as Finney-Smith receives the ball.
Finney-Smith (BKN) establishes his right foot as his pivot foot, which he lifts and re-plants before elevating to shoot.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) jumps alongside Finney-Smith's (BKN) path and legally contests the shot near the rim.

After deflecting the ball, Finney-Smith's (BKN) forearm makes some contact with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) head during rebounding.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Thomas (BKN) commits a take foul on Lillard (MIL).
Antetokounmpo (MIL) makes contact with the ball, and with the part of Thomas' (BKN) hand that is on the ball, as he contests the driving shot attempt.
Bridges (BKN) commits a take foul on Lillard (MIL).
O'Neale (BKN) commits a take foul on Crowder (MIL).
Lillard (MIL) brings his forearm towards Bridges' (BKN) path and marginal contact occurs off ball during the inbound.
Bridges (BKN) brings his arm towards Lillard's (MIL) slightly extended forearm, and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
